t/embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/$version$/tomcat-embed-websocket-$version$-sources.jar\\\",\\n    51\\t    \\\"repository-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/apache/tomcat\\\",\\n    52\\t    \\\"test-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/apache/tomcat/tree/$version$/test/org/apache/tomcat/websocket\\\",\\n    53\\t    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/apache/tomcat/blob/$version$/webapps/docs/web-socket-howto.xml\\\",\\n    54\\t    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Tomcat Embed WebSocket provides Apache Tomcat's embeddable implementation of the Jakarta WebSocket 2.0 API for Tomcat 10 applications. It enables WebSocket client and server endpoints, message handling, session management, and Tomcat-specific WebSocket configuration when running Tomcat embedded in a JVM application.\\\",\\n    55\\t    \\\"tested-versions\\\" : [\\n    56\\t      \\\"10.0.0\\\"\\n    57\\t    ],\\n    58\\t    \\\"allowed-packages\\\" : [\\n    59\\t      \\\"jakarta.websocket\\\",\\n    60\\t      \\\"org.apache.tomcat.websocket\\\"\\n    61\\t    ]\\n    62\\t  }\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_45\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'git status --short -- metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/index.json metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/10.0.0/reachability-metadata.json tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/10.0.0/user-code-filter.json'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_45\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'git status --short -- metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/index.json metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/10.0.0/reachability-metadata.json tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/10.0.0/user-code-filter.json'\",\"aggregated_output\":\" M metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/index.json\\n M tests/src/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/10.0.0/user-code-filter.json\\n?? metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/10.0.0/reachability-metadata.json\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_46\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Added the missing `10.0.0` reachability metadata in [reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/6381-e90c027e/metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/10.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:1) for `META-INF/services/org.apache.juli.logging.Log`, conditioned on `org.apache.tomcat.websocket.WsWebSocketContainer`. I also corrected the `10.0.0` package namespace in [index.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/6381-e90c027e/metadata/org.apache.tomcat.embed/tomcat-embed-websocket/index.json:49) from `javax.websocket` to `jakarta.websocket`, which is the Tomcat 10 namespace.\\n\\nAll reproduction and verification commands were run with `GRAALVM_HOME` and `JAVA_HOME` set to `/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/vj/forge/ce/sdk/latest_graalvm_home`, and `native-image --version` matched the required `25.0.2` / `Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+10.1`. The exact `runNativeTraceImage` command you provided passed on rerun with 19/19 native tests successful. `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:10.0.0` also passed, and after the final `index.json` correction, `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.apache.tomcat.embed:tomcat-embed-websocket:10.0.0` still passed.\\n\\nOne additional worktree change is present in [user-code-filter.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge4/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/6381-e90c027e/tests/src/org.ap